p: Another recent paper examined a commercial EO from the United States of America, which, although dominated by β-ocimene (36.4%), showed an uncharacteristically high content of limonene (26.9%), as well as high ( Z)-tagetone content (16.9%), also observed in Rwanda EOs, in addition to a relatively high content of alloocimene (6.3%) and β-caryophyllene (4.5%), and relatively low amounts of ( Z)-tagetenone (0.8%) and ( E)-tagetenone (0.6%) [ 80].
